# My Research Interests

Describe your research interests here. The AI will use this to filter and
rank arXiv papers by relevance to you. Be as specific or broad as you like.

## Example

I work on **beyond the Standard Model (BSM) phenomenology**, with a focus on:

- Supersymmetry (SUSY) and its signatures at the LHC
- Dark matter models (WIMPs, axions, sterile neutrinos)
- Effective field theory (EFT) approaches to new physics
- Flavor physics and CP violation
- Collider phenomenology: Higgs boson properties, diboson production

I am also interested in:

- Lattice QCD results relevant to flavor physics
- Neutrino mass models and leptogenesis
- Machine learning applications in particle physics

I am **not** interested in:

- Pure string theory / formal developments without phenomenological applications
- Astrophysical observations (unless directly related to dark matter detection)
